org.openbel.framework.core.df.beldata
Interface BELDataHeaderHandler

public interface BELDataHeaderHandler

BELDataHeaderHandler defines a parser handler to interpret header blocks and block properties coming from the BELDataHeaderParser. It is intended for the class implementation of BELDataHeaderHandler to interpret the values.

Author:
Anthony Bargnesi <abargnesi@selventa.com>

Method Detail

onHeaderBlock

void onHeaderBlock(String headerBlock,
                   long tokenStartOffset)
                   throws AbortParsingException
Process a headerBlock coming from the BELDataHeaderParser. This operation is called when a BELData file header block has been read. To abort processing of the file after this point throw AbortParsingException.

Parameters:
headerBlock - String, the header block just parsed from BELDataHeaderParser
tokenStartOffset - long, the offset in the file to the start of the header block token
Throws:
AbortParsingException, - can be thrown by the class implementation to stop parsing
AbortParsingException

onBlockProperty

void onBlockProperty(String propertyKey,
                     String propertyValue,
                     long tokenStartOffset)
                     throws AbortParsingException
Process a propertyKey and propertyValue coming from the BELDataHeaderParser. This operation is called when a BELDData file header property has been read. To abort processing of the file after this point throw AbortParsingException.

Parameters:
propertyKey - String, the property key just parsed from BELDataHeaderParser
propertyValue - String, the property value just parsed from BELDataHeaderParser
tokenStartOffset - long, the offset in the file to the start of the block property
Throws:
AbortParsingException, - can be thrown by the class implementation to stop parsing
AbortParsingException
